𝗧𝗼𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗥𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗻𝘂𝗲 𝗯𝘆 𝗥𝗲𝗴𝗶𝗼𝗻:
=SUMIF(Financial_tbl[Region], L6, Financial_tbl[Revenue])

𝗔𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗘𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗯𝘆 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁 𝗖𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗴𝗼𝗿𝘆:
=AVERAGEIF(Financial_tbl[Product_Category], L14, Financial_tbl[Marketing_Spend])

𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗛𝗶𝗴𝗵𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗳𝗶𝘁:
=MAX(Financial_tbl[Profit])
=XLOOKUP(L22, Financial_tbl[Profit], Financial_tbl[Date])
Alternatively, for the date with the highest customer count:
=MAX(Financial_tbl[Customer_Count])
=INDEX(Financial_tbl[Date], MATCH(L34, Financial_tbl[Customer_Count], 0))

𝗙𝗶𝗹𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗥𝗲𝗴𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁 𝗖𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗴𝗼𝗿𝘆 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗗𝗿𝗼𝗽-𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗟𝗶𝘀𝘁𝘀 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗧𝗼𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗖𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿 𝗖𝗼𝘂𝗻𝘁
=SUMIFS(Financial_tbl[Customer_Count], Financial_tbl[Region], L27, Financial_tbl[Product_Category], M27)

𝗞𝗲𝘆 𝗙𝗶𝗻𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀:
• Revenue Performance:
 - July was a high-performing month. February, April, and September saw reduced sales, while the remainder of the year showed steady revenue levels, indicating consistent consumer demand.
• Cost Trends:
- February costs were low which aligns with the low revenue, cost remained consistent throughout the year, reflecting effective management and operational efficiency.
• Regional Product Performance:
 - Clothing demonstrated strong sales in the East and South. Furniture showed strong sales in the North and South, highlighting regional preferences.
